  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bees Saving Elephants in Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Elephant crop raiding poses serious economic &amp; conservation problems in Kenya. Farmers often retaliate in an effort to protect their crops, &amp; both humans &amp; elephants suffer severe injuries &amp; death as a result. We are using beehive fences in Kenya as a form of human-elephant conflict mitigation to reduce human elephant conflict, allow rangers to shift their focus to anti-poaching, &amp; allow farmers to increase crop yield, harvest honey for consumption or to sell for income.</narrative>
  </description>
